Genitalia
: Male: Median process of pygophore medium sized (
Fig. 75
), with rounded apex (
Fig. 70
). Both parameres with medium sized setae on dorsal and ventral surfaces, with distinct, sharp curved process in apical part (
Figs. 71–74
). Right paramere slightly smaller and thinner than left paramere, narrow in basal part and rounded in apical part. Pedicel relatively short and distinctly bent laterally (
Figs. 76–78
). Basal lobe of dorsal phallothecal sclerite enlarged on left side (
Figs. 76–78
).

Female
: Valvifer I rounded with dense, variably-sized (mostly long) setae (
Fig. 69
). Styloids with delicately rounded apices and short, numerous, robust setae on inner margin (
Fig. 67
). Valvula II convolute inwards with widely rounded apex and with two lateral indentations below (
Fig. 68
).
